[2]
Date: Thu, 17 June 2004
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak Reports [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_06_17a/en/>

Leptospirosis in Kenya
-----------------------
The Ministry of Health, Kenya has reported a total number of 141 suspected
cases including 6 deaths of leptospirosis in a high school in Bungoma
district. Leptospirosis has been laboratory-confirmed. A nearby primary
school has also reported suspected cases and 2 deaths.
Environment, epidemiology and laboratory teams from the Ministry of Health
are working with district teams on investigations, with support from WHO.
For more information:
Human leptospirosis: guidance for diagnosis, surveillance and control
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/en/WHO_CDS_CSR_EPH_2002.23.pdf>
